WEBVTT


00:00:10.980 --> 00:00:13.313
RAMPANT ABUSE AT CHIBA NURSING HOME

00:00:13.396 --> 00:00:14.605
"A HOLE IN YOUR STOMACH"

00:00:14.688 --> 00:00:15.938
What is this article?

00:00:16.021 --> 00:00:17.021
FORCE-FED COLD CURRY

00:00:18.688 --> 00:00:20.105
And there are even videos.

00:00:21.813 --> 00:00:24.105
Hello, Mr. ********.

00:00:24.188 --> 00:00:26.563
It's delicious, isn't it?
Open your mouth wider.

00:00:26.646 --> 00:00:28.355
PERSON A SOUNDS LIKE HE'S GROANING

00:00:28.438 --> 00:00:30.896
-Don't waste it. Eat it all.
-This is the worst.

00:00:30.980 --> 00:00:31.980
We're checking

00:00:32.063 --> 00:00:34.271
if the source is
a resident's family member

00:00:34.355 --> 00:00:36.646
or one of our staff.

00:00:37.521 --> 00:00:40.980
Do your job so our nursing home
doesn't receive a government penalty.

00:00:50.480 --> 00:00:52.396
Mr. Sugawara,

00:00:52.980 --> 00:00:55.521
you shouldn't talk
to your elders like that.

00:00:57.980 --> 00:00:59.313
I'm sorry.

00:01:00.146 --> 00:01:02.063
It's just that this is an emergency.

00:01:03.188 --> 00:01:06.813
Now that the media
has released an article like this,

00:01:06.896 --> 00:01:08.521
even the risk-averse authorities

00:01:08.605 --> 00:01:09.646
will take action.

00:01:10.730 --> 00:01:13.063
It'll be hard to avoid
a business suspension.

00:01:13.146 --> 00:01:13.980
Sir.

00:01:16.313 --> 00:01:22.730
We were forcing Mr. Iemori
to practice writing his will.

00:01:24.230 --> 00:01:27.105
What would happen
if that video went public?

00:01:27.605 --> 00:01:29.896
A video of you forcing him to practice?

00:01:30.396 --> 00:01:33.271
-Such a thing exists?!
-I'm just asking, if it existed…

00:01:33.355 --> 00:01:37.063
Young people these days
film anything and everything.

00:01:37.146 --> 00:01:38.980
Sir, please calm down.

00:01:39.063 --> 00:01:40.646
I'm just asking, if it existed…

00:01:40.730 --> 00:01:43.980
If such a thing comes out,
it won't be just a business suspension.

00:01:44.063 --> 00:01:46.730
We'll both be finished.

00:01:49.813 --> 00:01:53.855
You, find out who was filming.

00:01:57.230 --> 00:01:58.105
I…

00:02:00.438 --> 00:02:03.855
have an idea
of who is pulling the strings.

00:02:10.980 --> 00:02:13.146
Damn Kujo.

00:02:13.230 --> 00:02:14.396
That bastard!

00:02:14.480 --> 00:02:16.730
Oh, ouch! Ow, ow!

00:02:21.146 --> 00:02:24.105
How many times are you going to fail?
Finish it quickly.

00:02:24.188 --> 00:02:27.313
So the USB you received from Mibu

00:02:27.396 --> 00:02:29.230
had this video on it, huh?

00:02:29.313 --> 00:02:30.230
Yes.

00:02:30.896 --> 00:02:33.688
How did you know
that Mibu would be able to get this?

00:02:35.146 --> 00:02:37.521
I remembered that we'd met before.

00:02:38.146 --> 00:02:39.605
Met who?

00:02:41.063 --> 00:02:44.021
More importantly,
you should eat too, Attorney Karasuma.

00:02:44.521 --> 00:02:46.896
Junk food in the morning?

00:02:46.980 --> 00:02:48.480
Did you give up on autophagy?

00:02:48.563 --> 00:02:49.521
Yes.

00:02:51.230 --> 00:02:53.938
It's because today
is going to be a busy day.

00:02:54.021 --> 00:02:54.855
Busy?

00:02:56.146 --> 00:02:57.980
More importantly, Attorney Karasuma,

00:02:58.063 --> 00:03:01.146
could you contact the person
who wrote that article again?

00:03:32.355 --> 00:03:33.605
Kuga,

00:03:34.313 --> 00:03:37.105
did you leak it to the media?

00:03:40.896 --> 00:03:42.980
I think very highly of you.

00:03:45.938 --> 00:03:47.563
Now's the time to fess up.

00:03:50.646 --> 00:03:51.896
I…

00:03:53.271 --> 00:03:54.896
don't know anything.

00:03:56.230 --> 00:03:57.230
But,

00:03:58.146 --> 00:03:59.896
Mr. Sugawara,

00:04:00.396 --> 00:04:03.855
you wouldn't believe me anyway.

00:04:04.771 --> 00:04:06.688
Do as you please.

00:04:09.730 --> 00:04:11.271
I see.

00:04:12.688 --> 00:04:17.021
The reason the government created
the medical system and social insurance

00:04:17.105 --> 00:04:21.646
wasn't to save the vulnerable
or increase the happiness of the people.

00:04:21.730 --> 00:04:25.480
It was to keep the people healthy
so they could make them work a lot,

00:04:26.896 --> 00:04:29.480
thereby strengthening the country.

00:04:35.813 --> 00:04:38.188
But times have changed.

00:04:40.771 --> 00:04:44.896
Unnecessary people
are guaranteed to be discarded.

00:05:11.521 --> 00:05:13.063
Hello, Mr. Kuga.

00:05:14.563 --> 00:05:16.813
We're from the Honjo Police Station.

00:05:16.896 --> 00:05:19.980
Your doctor filed a report,
so we came to ask a few questions.

00:05:21.480 --> 00:05:25.605
I'm sorry, but I got drunk
and fell asleep on the street.

00:05:25.688 --> 00:05:26.771
Now I'm here.

00:05:27.813 --> 00:05:28.938
So what happened?

00:05:29.021 --> 00:05:31.438
Well, I don't remember at all.

00:05:32.646 --> 00:05:34.396
Contact us if you remember.

00:05:34.480 --> 00:05:35.855
Okay.

00:05:36.938 --> 00:05:40.813
Excuse me. Can you tell us
a little more about his injuries?

00:05:40.896 --> 00:05:43.355
Understood. I'll show you
to the conference room.

00:05:57.605 --> 00:06:00.688
Sugawara planted a bug
in the hospital room,

00:06:00.771 --> 00:06:02.438
so I'm messaging you.

00:06:02.521 --> 00:06:04.896
He's still suspicious of me,

00:06:04.980 --> 00:06:06.938
but I think I'm okay for now.

00:06:08.438 --> 00:06:11.396
The article about Mr. Iemori is crazy.

00:06:11.480 --> 00:06:13.938
That damn Sugawara was really pissed off.

00:06:17.063 --> 00:06:18.063
GOOD JOB.

00:06:18.146 --> 00:06:20.646
ARE YOU DOING OKAY, KUGA?
DOES IT HURT MUCH?

00:06:21.855 --> 00:06:23.813
It hurts like hell…

00:06:26.188 --> 00:06:27.521
Mibu.

00:06:32.771 --> 00:06:34.230
Oh, hello, Mr. Sugawara.

00:06:35.230 --> 00:06:36.313
Yes?

00:06:37.063 --> 00:06:39.646
Have you nailed down
who leaked the videos?

00:06:40.230 --> 00:06:42.105
No, not yet.

00:06:42.188 --> 00:06:45.646
I put the most suspicious guy
in the hospital and planted a bug.

00:06:45.730 --> 00:06:46.605
Huh?

00:06:46.688 --> 00:06:48.521
Put him in the hospital?

00:06:48.605 --> 00:06:50.021
Are you out of your mind?

00:06:50.105 --> 00:06:53.688
The abuse videos
were all over the news online.

00:06:53.771 --> 00:06:56.146
The media is going to hound you.

00:06:56.813 --> 00:07:01.605
The press has already crowded the front
of our facility, creating a commotion.

00:07:01.688 --> 00:07:04.355
I can't get close to my home
or my mistress's place.

00:07:04.938 --> 00:07:06.938
What should we do about this?

00:07:08.355 --> 00:07:11.605
The police will investigate
since there are videos.

00:07:12.980 --> 00:07:17.105
If they find out the CEO has gang ties,
it'll blow up big time.

00:07:17.188 --> 00:07:19.646
What do we do about the guy
in the flicking video?

00:07:20.230 --> 00:07:25.063
If it were only the flicking, the person
would just get reported without detention.

00:07:25.146 --> 00:07:26.563
But

00:07:27.521 --> 00:07:31.146
if the entire facility is suspected
of being involved in abuse,

00:07:31.938 --> 00:07:34.063
even you will be in a precarious position.

00:07:35.271 --> 00:07:36.855
Besides what's been leaked,

00:07:36.938 --> 00:07:39.938
if more videos get out
of you forcing anyone to write a will,

00:07:40.021 --> 00:07:41.438
you'll be completely ruined.

00:07:41.938 --> 00:07:46.938
You and I both will be arrested
for compulsion and breach of trust.

00:07:51.938 --> 00:07:53.396
Attorney Yamashiro.

00:07:55.188 --> 00:07:56.896
May I have a moment?

00:07:58.730 --> 00:08:00.605
I'm Ms. Ichida from The Toei Shimbun.

00:08:00.688 --> 00:08:01.521
REPORTER

00:08:02.938 --> 00:08:07.480
You're the retained lawyer for the general
incorporated association Kikogi. Correct?

00:08:08.105 --> 00:08:11.730
I'd like to ask you
about the coercion of a will.

00:08:13.813 --> 00:08:14.688
Sir!

00:08:15.271 --> 00:08:17.230
Could you give us a few words?

00:08:17.313 --> 00:08:20.188
Shut up! You're only a reporter.

00:08:25.271 --> 00:08:27.521
If you spread false information,
I'll sue you.

00:08:28.021 --> 00:08:29.771
Are you ready for that?

00:08:33.730 --> 00:08:35.271
Don't follow me.

00:08:35.355 --> 00:08:37.896
I'm glad the article went viral,
Ms. Ichida.

00:08:38.563 --> 00:08:41.396
As soon as I released the scoop
that you told me about,

00:08:41.480 --> 00:08:43.396
all the other companies followed.

00:08:43.980 --> 00:08:49.271
If I release the second article
about a big-time lawyer helping a gang,

00:08:49.355 --> 00:08:51.105
it'll go even more viral.

00:08:55.813 --> 00:08:58.230
Ms. Ichida from The Toei Shimbun
was very happy.

00:08:58.855 --> 00:09:00.105
Is that so?

00:09:01.438 --> 00:09:04.480
You sure know a lot of people,
Attorney Karasuma.

00:09:04.563 --> 00:09:05.438
Huh?

00:09:05.521 --> 00:09:06.646
Not as many as you.

00:09:06.730 --> 00:09:07.938
No, no.

00:09:08.021 --> 00:09:12.771
The only contacts I have
are sinister-looking people with tattoos.

00:09:16.063 --> 00:09:18.105
Conversely, you, Attorney Karasuma,

00:09:18.605 --> 00:09:23.063
know people who are mostly clean
and, on top of that, are women.

00:09:23.938 --> 00:09:26.313
Hmm. Well, I guess you're right.

00:09:27.938 --> 00:09:30.771
We're both attorneys,
so why the difference?

00:09:35.938 --> 00:09:37.021
"Our faces"?

00:09:37.105 --> 00:09:38.021
Huh?

00:09:38.105 --> 00:09:39.980
That's what you wanted to say, right?

00:09:41.188 --> 00:09:44.021
You just said it yourself.

00:09:44.105 --> 00:09:45.105
It's a coincidence.

00:09:45.188 --> 00:09:46.938
It's not a coincidence.

00:09:47.021 --> 00:09:50.271
Ms. Yakushimae ignores me
when I ask her out.

00:09:50.355 --> 00:09:53.021
But you two go
to that Chinese place all the time.

00:09:53.105 --> 00:09:56.438
You only asked her out
to the "Japan's top takoyaki" place.

00:09:56.521 --> 00:09:59.105
That doesn't count as asking someone out.

00:09:59.188 --> 00:10:00.188
Is that no good?

00:10:00.271 --> 00:10:03.063
No. I can't believe
you were ever able to get married.

00:10:04.188 --> 00:10:06.563
"That's why you got divorced."

00:10:06.646 --> 00:10:08.646
That's what you wanted to say, right?

00:10:09.146 --> 00:10:11.063
You said it yourself again.

00:10:11.605 --> 00:10:13.313
Hey, Kujo!

00:10:15.521 --> 00:10:18.146
I knew you'd come here,
Attorney Yamashiro.

00:10:18.230 --> 00:10:20.021
You knew?

00:10:20.105 --> 00:10:22.021
I thought it was time you showed up.

00:10:22.605 --> 00:10:23.938
Nice to meet you. I'm--

00:10:24.021 --> 00:10:25.438
Shut up.

00:10:26.021 --> 00:10:29.521
You used the trash media
to pull off a dirty move.

00:10:31.146 --> 00:10:32.396
But, well,

00:10:32.896 --> 00:10:35.980
you did better than I expected,
Attorney Kujo.

00:10:36.813 --> 00:10:39.271
I don't know how much evidence you have,

00:10:40.313 --> 00:10:42.355
but why don't we end it here?

00:10:43.521 --> 00:10:46.396
It's not like you enjoy
cornering me, right?

00:10:50.646 --> 00:10:53.438
I'll pay back
Ms. Iemori's entire inheritance.

00:10:54.896 --> 00:10:57.646
You win, Attorney Kujo.

00:11:00.646 --> 00:11:03.188
Understood. I'll end it.

00:11:04.771 --> 00:11:06.146
But in exchange…

00:11:08.146 --> 00:11:09.521
please take off your badge.

00:11:09.605 --> 00:11:10.646
Huh?

00:11:12.771 --> 00:11:15.063
I want you to quit being an attorney.

00:11:16.355 --> 00:11:18.271
You bastard.

00:11:18.355 --> 00:11:21.480
I show a little humility,
and you start acting cocky.

00:11:22.146 --> 00:11:23.938
I'm your former mentor.

00:11:24.563 --> 00:11:26.646
How dare you tell me to remove my badge!

00:11:26.730 --> 00:11:28.021
Don't you screw with me!

00:11:29.563 --> 00:11:31.521
I'll crush you completely.

00:11:31.605 --> 00:11:34.730
I'll show you how outclassed you are.

00:11:37.646 --> 00:11:39.063
Understood.

00:11:43.730 --> 00:11:46.146
Then let's go all-out.

00:11:49.605 --> 00:11:51.021
Come at me.

00:11:51.105 --> 00:11:54.230
I'm not going down yet.

00:11:55.063 --> 00:11:59.730
It's ridiculous to think
that attorneys have power.

00:12:00.396 --> 00:12:03.438
The ones with money have power, right?

00:12:03.521 --> 00:12:04.855
Am I wrong?

00:12:05.563 --> 00:12:07.438
It makes you wonder…

00:12:07.938 --> 00:12:12.938
Strong attorneys
only take on clients with money.

00:12:13.646 --> 00:12:15.355
The poor can only choose

00:12:15.438 --> 00:12:18.813
court-appointed attorneys
from who-knows-where.

00:12:20.355 --> 00:12:24.313
They lose cases they should've won
because the attorney didn't even try.

00:12:25.813 --> 00:12:28.105
Even if we're all equal under the law,

00:12:28.605 --> 00:12:31.980
we're clearly divided before it.

00:12:32.063 --> 00:12:33.646
What do you think?

00:12:35.605 --> 00:12:38.021
Regardless of whether
the client is rich or poor,

00:12:38.105 --> 00:12:40.480
I charge a flat retainer fee
of 330,000 yen.

00:12:40.980 --> 00:12:42.146
Status isn't a concern.

00:12:42.230 --> 00:12:45.021
330,000 yen?

00:12:45.105 --> 00:12:48.521
And I don't accept any rewards for bail.
That's my policy.

00:12:49.188 --> 00:12:51.813
But many people still say
that's too expensive.

00:12:51.896 --> 00:12:53.313
What the hell?

00:12:53.396 --> 00:12:55.271
Are you running a discount store?

00:12:55.980 --> 00:13:00.438
You've gotta rip off the rich
and the troublemakers, right?

00:13:00.521 --> 00:13:02.896
I've never seen
such a people-pleasing attorney.

00:13:03.646 --> 00:13:05.355
It makes you wonder…

00:13:06.688 --> 00:13:07.980
I can see it now.

00:13:09.855 --> 00:13:12.313
"He who fights with monsters
should be careful

00:13:12.896 --> 00:13:15.480
lest he thereby become a monster."

00:13:17.771 --> 00:13:20.188
"And if you gaze long into an abyss,

00:13:20.271 --> 00:13:21.980
the abyss also…

00:13:24.605 --> 00:13:26.105
gazes into you."

00:13:33.771 --> 00:13:36.355
Nietzsche's Beyond Good and Evil?

00:13:37.730 --> 00:13:40.313
You brought up a pretty overused quote.

00:14:23.646 --> 00:14:25.521
Even now,

00:14:25.605 --> 00:14:29.230
I respect you, Attorney Yamashiro,
for how you guided me.

00:14:55.980 --> 00:14:59.396
One of your guys filed
a police report for assault.

00:15:00.063 --> 00:15:04.396
Since the video of you
beating us up went viral,

00:15:04.480 --> 00:15:07.313
we only filed the report
because the cops told us to.

00:15:07.813 --> 00:15:08.896
Hmm…

00:15:08.980 --> 00:15:11.063
Withdraw it immediately.

00:15:11.563 --> 00:15:12.688
Yes.

00:15:12.771 --> 00:15:14.896
I'll have it withdrawn immediately.

00:15:16.938 --> 00:15:20.438
You cooked all of this up,
didn't you, Mibu?

00:15:22.605 --> 00:15:23.896
What?

00:15:23.980 --> 00:15:26.063
I have no idea what you're talking about.

00:15:26.146 --> 00:15:27.980
Remember,

00:15:28.730 --> 00:15:31.771
I'll make sure to return the favor.

00:15:32.521 --> 00:15:33.355
MR. SUGAWARA

00:15:35.730 --> 00:15:37.730
Did Sugawara find out about me?

00:15:37.813 --> 00:15:39.313
No, he didn't.

00:15:41.105 --> 00:15:42.563
That's good.

00:15:42.646 --> 00:15:45.021
But more importantly,
you're amazing, Kuga.

00:15:45.105 --> 00:15:47.605
You infiltrated that facility
and never got caught.

00:15:47.688 --> 00:15:50.730
No, your discerning eye
is even more amazing.

00:15:50.813 --> 00:15:54.188
You had me sneak into the facility
to find Sugawara's weakness.

00:15:54.271 --> 00:15:55.521
Weakness?

00:15:55.605 --> 00:15:58.063
I'm not looking for something so small.

00:15:59.605 --> 00:16:02.521
I don't hold a personal grudge
against Sugawara.

00:16:03.396 --> 00:16:06.938
I just used him
to get bigger in this world.

00:16:07.771 --> 00:16:08.938
I see.

00:16:10.230 --> 00:16:11.688
Thank you.

00:16:13.563 --> 00:16:16.980
But more importantly, good job
getting your hands on that video.

00:16:17.063 --> 00:16:18.521
Well, I mean…

00:16:20.855 --> 00:16:23.980
I got lucky because the damage
didn't touch the data.

00:16:24.938 --> 00:16:25.855
Thanks to that,

00:16:25.938 --> 00:16:30.355
I was able to get rid of Sugawara
and repay my debt to Attorney Kujo.

00:16:32.646 --> 00:16:36.480
But I'm surprised
that Attorney Kujo remembered me.

00:16:37.063 --> 00:16:40.230
I think we only met once at your place.

00:16:41.396 --> 00:16:43.063
He's just like that.

00:16:44.646 --> 00:16:46.230
Anyway, it's all thanks to you.

00:16:46.313 --> 00:16:48.021
Go to a hot spring for a while.

00:16:48.521 --> 00:16:49.813
Thank you.

00:16:50.313 --> 00:16:54.563
But if it's an order from you, Mibu,
I'll do anything and give it my all.

00:16:54.646 --> 00:16:56.355
-Is that so?
-Yes.

00:16:58.646 --> 00:16:59.605
Well, then,

00:17:00.438 --> 00:17:03.521
shall we play human bowling,
like you did with Sugawara?

00:17:05.605 --> 00:17:07.855
I just got my nose cast taken off.

00:17:07.938 --> 00:17:09.813
Please give me a break.

00:17:12.605 --> 00:17:17.605
LAND FOR SALE
FEEL FREE TO CONTACT US

00:17:24.938 --> 00:17:27.646
The land our father left behind…

00:17:27.730 --> 00:17:29.855
I feel better now that it's a vacant lot.

00:17:30.563 --> 00:17:33.938
Sorry for making you do all this
when you're so busy, Hanae.

00:17:34.021 --> 00:17:35.271
It's nothing.

00:17:36.230 --> 00:17:38.563
Anyway, the lawyer you hired is amazing.

00:17:38.646 --> 00:17:41.146
We paid him money, so he just did his job.

00:17:41.230 --> 00:17:44.646
Money? His fee was really cheap.

00:17:44.730 --> 00:17:47.396
He got back the entire
400 million inheritance.

00:17:47.480 --> 00:17:50.271
Normally, the standard cut
would be 40 million.

00:17:50.355 --> 00:17:52.980
But he didn't even take half.
Only 10 million, right?

00:17:53.063 --> 00:17:55.771
That's unheard of.

00:18:01.896 --> 00:18:02.813
What?

00:18:03.313 --> 00:18:04.855
Oh, uh…

00:18:05.563 --> 00:18:07.396
It's hard to bring this up,

00:18:07.480 --> 00:18:11.480
but the 25 million yen you received
as a lifetime gift from Dad…

00:18:11.980 --> 00:18:15.063
Can you reflect that
in the inheritance distribution?

00:18:16.938 --> 00:18:19.396
Saeko gave you
a firm reminder to ask me, huh?

00:18:20.188 --> 00:18:23.855
Do what you want. I'm not obsessed
with the money enough to fight over it.

00:18:24.855 --> 00:18:25.980
Sorry about that.

00:18:27.355 --> 00:18:28.688
I don't care.

00:18:29.771 --> 00:18:31.771
The house is gone.

00:18:32.271 --> 00:18:34.980
I don't think I'll ever
have to talk to you guys again.

00:18:37.855 --> 00:18:40.396
That reminds me.
I just remembered something.

00:18:40.896 --> 00:18:44.146
Dad said something at Mom's funeral.

00:18:44.646 --> 00:18:47.271
He said that you've hated him
for a long time.

00:18:48.896 --> 00:18:50.188
What?

00:18:50.271 --> 00:18:51.396
You don't remember?

00:18:51.480 --> 00:18:55.271
You used to study in the kitchen a lot
when you were in junior high, right?

00:18:55.355 --> 00:18:57.480
I could concentrate there.

00:18:57.980 --> 00:19:01.563
That was when Mom and Dad
were at their worst.

00:19:02.063 --> 00:19:04.688
Dad didn't feel comfortable at home,

00:19:04.771 --> 00:19:06.938
so he would stop by a bar every night.

00:19:07.021 --> 00:19:09.063
When he came home drunk,

00:19:09.146 --> 00:19:13.396
you would go to your room
like you were running away.

00:19:14.688 --> 00:19:18.105
He said that you'd hated him
for as long as he could remember.

00:19:22.146 --> 00:19:24.938
I just remembered that
because the land is vacant now.

00:19:25.021 --> 00:19:26.605
There's no deeper meaning.

00:19:27.521 --> 00:19:28.730
I see.

00:19:30.521 --> 00:19:32.438
How much longer will you keep talking?

00:19:32.521 --> 00:19:33.771
I'm coming.

00:19:34.271 --> 00:19:37.271
Well, I'll leave the task
of inheritance distribution to you.

00:19:41.688 --> 00:19:43.938
That's actually not true.

00:19:45.355 --> 00:19:47.355
I was in the kitchen because…

00:19:54.063 --> 00:19:55.896
Hi, there.

00:20:01.021 --> 00:20:02.313
Ms. Yakushimae?

00:20:03.521 --> 00:20:05.355
Is today Halloween?

00:20:05.438 --> 00:20:07.521
No, I'm not in a costume.

00:20:09.771 --> 00:20:12.813
I bet you've never been popular
with the girls.

00:20:12.896 --> 00:20:13.855
Right.

00:20:14.855 --> 00:20:16.438
So how can I help you?

00:20:16.521 --> 00:20:19.313
I heard from Attorney Karasuma.

00:20:20.146 --> 00:20:23.646
You want to go out to eat with me, right?

00:20:24.355 --> 00:20:25.188
Eat?

00:20:25.271 --> 00:20:26.688
You said so yourself.

00:20:26.771 --> 00:20:29.771
You said that when you ask her out,
she never goes with you.

00:20:29.855 --> 00:20:31.355
Did I say that?

00:20:31.438 --> 00:20:33.313
I don't mind going with you.

00:20:33.396 --> 00:20:36.438
But only to a counter-only
sushi restaurant

00:20:36.521 --> 00:20:39.980
or a teppanyaki restaurant where
the chef cooks right in front of you.

00:20:40.063 --> 00:20:43.355
Sorry, we have a lot of work remaining
from Ms. Iemori's case.

00:20:44.355 --> 00:20:45.188
Hmm?

00:20:46.188 --> 00:20:47.480
Isn't that over already?

00:20:48.855 --> 00:20:51.105
A neighbor told me.

00:20:51.730 --> 00:20:53.230
The house was demolished.

00:20:53.813 --> 00:20:56.230
And she split the inheritance
with her brother.

00:20:56.313 --> 00:20:58.396
-All of it?
-Yeah.

00:20:58.480 --> 00:20:59.855
When her neighbor told her,

00:20:59.938 --> 00:21:04.813
"Since you did most of the caregiving,
you should've taken all of it,"

00:21:05.313 --> 00:21:07.063
she replied, "We're family."

00:21:08.980 --> 00:21:14.063
Truly, she seems to have prioritized
her family over herself

00:21:14.146 --> 00:21:15.146
until the very end.

00:21:21.646 --> 00:21:24.105
So, which restaurant are we going to?

00:21:24.188 --> 00:21:27.271
I only go to restaurants
with more than four stars on Tabelog.

00:21:27.355 --> 00:21:29.771
Attorney Karasuma, can you two go?

00:21:29.855 --> 00:21:30.688
What?

00:21:30.771 --> 00:21:32.271
-What about you?
-I have to go.

00:21:32.355 --> 00:21:35.313
Hey, hey. Don't run away,
you crooked lawyer.

00:21:35.396 --> 00:21:36.688
Treat me!

00:21:42.771 --> 00:21:43.980
Ms. Iemori.

00:21:45.396 --> 00:21:47.021
Attorney Kujo.

00:21:47.521 --> 00:21:49.355
Sorry for suddenly calling you here.

00:21:49.438 --> 00:21:51.563
Oh, no, no. What's this about?

00:21:51.646 --> 00:21:53.646
I wanted to give you the invoice.

00:21:54.146 --> 00:21:57.355
You could've just mailed it to me.

00:21:57.438 --> 00:21:59.188
Well, yes, but…

00:21:59.271 --> 00:22:00.396
Here you go.

00:22:01.521 --> 00:22:02.480
Okay.

00:22:02.563 --> 00:22:04.146
Well, I'll be going now.

00:22:09.063 --> 00:22:09.938
Ms. Iemori.

00:22:13.813 --> 00:22:15.813
Do you have a moment?

00:22:19.813 --> 00:22:22.688
Could it be
that you're regretting it deep down?

00:22:24.771 --> 00:22:26.146
Regretting what?

00:22:26.896 --> 00:22:31.230
Not being able to take care
of your father until the end.

00:22:35.021 --> 00:22:38.396
Your true goal
wasn't to get the money back.

00:22:39.146 --> 00:22:43.146
But rather, you had no other way
of working through your emotions.

00:22:46.480 --> 00:22:49.188
I heard that your neighbors said

00:22:50.396 --> 00:22:54.063
that you took care of your father
with such devotion.

00:22:55.480 --> 00:22:58.480
They were worried
that you might collapse one day.

00:23:02.688 --> 00:23:05.021
My mentor used to say this…

00:23:06.646 --> 00:23:08.730
No matter how hard it becomes,

00:23:09.230 --> 00:23:11.605
he wouldn't want
to be a burden to his children.

00:23:12.563 --> 00:23:13.980
That's how parents feel.

00:23:16.980 --> 00:23:19.605
Even if your father
didn't say it out loud,

00:23:20.813 --> 00:23:23.896
I'm sure he was grateful to you,
from the bottom of his heart.

00:23:30.480 --> 00:23:32.355
You did your best, Ms. Iemori.

00:23:59.730 --> 00:24:01.063
My father…

00:24:03.396 --> 00:24:08.063
put up with all my selfishness

00:24:08.771 --> 00:24:11.521
when I was alone and lonely.

00:24:12.605 --> 00:24:14.563
He never said anything bad

00:24:14.646 --> 00:24:18.438
about my mother who left me.

00:24:20.021 --> 00:24:21.146
He was

00:24:23.146 --> 00:24:24.855
a kind dad.

00:24:29.521 --> 00:24:30.396
But…

00:24:33.313 --> 00:24:36.355
it seems he thought I hated him.

00:24:38.730 --> 00:24:40.188
But in reality,

00:24:41.688 --> 00:24:43.105
every night,

00:24:44.105 --> 00:24:46.896
I wondered if Dad would come home.

00:24:47.396 --> 00:24:49.230
I was worried.

00:24:49.730 --> 00:24:50.980
I was anxious.

00:24:51.771 --> 00:24:53.521
That's why I waited for him.

00:25:06.230 --> 00:25:08.730
I was never able
to clear up that misunderstanding.

00:25:11.438 --> 00:25:13.813
I never returned his love.

00:25:17.271 --> 00:25:21.105
And Dad passed away.

00:25:50.771 --> 00:25:53.938
This is the castella
that you and Dad liked, right?

00:25:56.063 --> 00:25:57.980
It's okay, Shinji.

00:25:58.063 --> 00:26:02.396
You're busy.
You don't have to come by so often.

00:26:03.396 --> 00:26:05.021
But I'm worried.

00:26:05.855 --> 00:26:07.146
I'm fine.

00:26:08.230 --> 00:26:10.646
It's too early for me to die alone.

00:26:13.021 --> 00:26:14.355
I'm glad.

00:26:16.438 --> 00:26:17.730
About what?

00:26:18.230 --> 00:26:21.438
Well, you must be doing well enough
to joke around like that.

00:26:21.938 --> 00:26:22.980
Here you go.

00:26:33.521 --> 00:26:34.813
How do you like it?

00:26:36.438 --> 00:26:37.771
It's delicious.

00:26:39.521 --> 00:26:41.480
Right?

00:26:52.146 --> 00:26:53.230
Hey, don't open that.

00:26:53.813 --> 00:26:57.230
-Let some fresh air in.
-If you open it, people will hear us.

00:26:57.313 --> 00:27:00.230
-They won't hear us.
-Just close it.

00:27:01.230 --> 00:27:04.980
Okay, okay. Understood.

00:27:05.063 --> 00:27:06.271
There you go.

00:27:09.521 --> 00:27:11.021
But, Mom,

00:27:11.605 --> 00:27:13.438
I know Dad is,

00:27:14.646 --> 00:27:16.813
but you and I are also victims.

00:27:18.396 --> 00:27:21.230
So we don't have
to live in fear like criminals.

00:27:23.021 --> 00:27:24.771
It's not too late, even now,

00:27:25.938 --> 00:27:27.396
so let's move forward.

00:27:30.563 --> 00:27:31.396
Okay?

00:27:34.396 --> 00:27:35.480
I wonder if I can.

00:27:35.563 --> 00:27:37.146
You can.

00:27:39.313 --> 00:27:40.938
I'm here for you.

00:27:45.730 --> 00:27:46.730
Okay.

00:27:53.938 --> 00:27:55.146
Down.

00:27:57.563 --> 00:27:58.771
Okay.

00:28:01.563 --> 00:28:02.980
Good job.

00:28:03.855 --> 00:28:05.438
Attorney Kujo,

00:28:05.521 --> 00:28:07.438
Mibu is here.

00:28:11.271 --> 00:28:12.605
Attorney Kujo,

00:28:12.688 --> 00:28:14.730
I've finally found an owner for it.

00:28:15.605 --> 00:28:18.771
Now the office won't get torn up anymore.

00:28:21.730 --> 00:28:23.230
Hey, Mibu.

00:28:23.313 --> 00:28:24.396
Yes?

00:28:27.605 --> 00:28:32.105
Would it be okay
if I became Black Thunder's owner?

00:28:33.396 --> 00:28:34.896
You want to keep it?

00:28:36.771 --> 00:28:39.730
It's already like family to me.

00:28:45.480 --> 00:28:46.313
Attorney Kujo…

00:28:48.605 --> 00:28:53.813
keeping a dog means taking care of a life.

00:28:54.313 --> 00:28:55.730
Do you understand that?

00:28:56.730 --> 00:28:57.730
I understand.

00:28:58.230 --> 00:29:00.021
Do you really understand?

00:29:01.188 --> 00:29:04.813
You have to walk it every day and
potty-train it. It might even bite you.

00:29:04.896 --> 00:29:07.021
You have to brush its coat and its teeth.

00:29:08.146 --> 00:29:11.730
I know you're worried
because you had Rice Cake, but…

00:29:17.771 --> 00:29:18.605
Excuse me.

00:29:21.105 --> 00:29:22.063
Hello?

00:29:23.063 --> 00:29:23.980
Yeah.

00:29:27.188 --> 00:29:28.980
Who's Rice Cake?

00:29:29.980 --> 00:29:32.063
The dog that Mibu used to have.

00:29:32.146 --> 00:29:35.146
So that's why he acts differently
when it comes to dogs.

00:29:35.230 --> 00:29:36.313
Yeah.

00:29:36.396 --> 00:29:39.146
But Mibu is right.
It's a lot of work to keep a dog.

00:29:39.230 --> 00:29:41.563
What if you have to go on a business trip?

00:29:43.563 --> 00:29:45.105
When that happens…

00:29:45.896 --> 00:29:48.063
-I'll ask you to take care of it.
-What?!

00:29:48.146 --> 00:29:52.188
I mean, why not? We're both single.

00:29:52.271 --> 00:29:54.063
We're practically family.

00:29:54.146 --> 00:29:58.188
No. Who's to say I'll be around forever?

00:29:58.938 --> 00:30:00.146
Attorney Kujo,

00:30:00.230 --> 00:30:02.063
I'd like to ask for your assistance.

00:30:03.563 --> 00:30:06.021
Someone who's taken care of me
has been arrested.

00:30:07.271 --> 00:30:08.646
I need a bit of help.

00:30:09.188 --> 00:30:11.605
I don't mind. Who is it?

00:30:12.938 --> 00:30:14.980
The underboss of Fushimi-gumi.

00:30:15.605 --> 00:30:17.230
Kiyoshi Kyogoku.

00:30:32.271 --> 00:30:33.938
Sir,

00:30:34.563 --> 00:30:40.521
I'm the victim who almost got
his brand-new watch stolen.

00:30:41.271 --> 00:30:43.563
Why am I the one who got arrested?

00:30:44.230 --> 00:30:45.271
Before we came here,

00:30:45.355 --> 00:30:48.855
we asked the detective
about the situation off-the-record.

00:30:49.521 --> 00:30:52.480
According to Kenichi Sakuma,
who filed the police report…

00:30:55.146 --> 00:30:59.521
he did run up to you,
but he didn't intend to steal anything.

00:30:59.605 --> 00:31:02.271
But you inflicted serious physical injury.

00:31:02.771 --> 00:31:05.730
The bodyguards were
the perpetrators of the injury.

00:31:05.813 --> 00:31:07.896
And you, Mr. Kyogoku, as their superior,

00:31:07.980 --> 00:31:10.813
will be charged
as a joint conspirator in the assault.

00:31:11.730 --> 00:31:14.188
But I was just trying to protect myself.

00:31:14.271 --> 00:31:15.938
You're an active yakuza member.

00:31:16.021 --> 00:31:18.855
For the police, this case
is a good excuse to arrest you.

00:31:19.438 --> 00:31:22.938
You want to settle this quickly
and shorten your detention period.

00:31:23.021 --> 00:31:24.021
The other guy won't.

00:31:26.230 --> 00:31:28.146
The yakuza aren't respected anymore.

00:31:28.230 --> 00:31:31.021
I saw the security camera footage
at the parking lot.

00:31:31.105 --> 00:31:34.855
The bodyguards will likely be seen
as having acted in self-defense.

00:31:34.938 --> 00:31:36.813
You won't be prosecuted, Mr. Kyogoku.

00:31:36.896 --> 00:31:39.480
I heard you helped
to cut loose a thug in 20 days,

00:31:39.563 --> 00:31:41.146
so I requested your assistance.

00:31:41.646 --> 00:31:44.063
Please get this over with quickly.

00:31:44.146 --> 00:31:46.230
It's up to you how quickly this ends.

00:31:46.313 --> 00:31:47.563
That's enough.

00:31:48.646 --> 00:31:50.896
Let me use your phone.
I wanna talk to my men.

00:31:50.980 --> 00:31:52.146
No, you can't.

00:31:52.730 --> 00:31:55.146
It's not in line
with an attorney-client meeting.

00:31:55.230 --> 00:31:57.396
Attorneys face
disciplinary action for that.

00:31:57.480 --> 00:31:59.730
Don't give me that garbage.

00:31:59.813 --> 00:32:02.563
Then, give Mibu a message for me.

00:32:03.063 --> 00:32:04.646
Lawyers are just

00:32:05.730 --> 00:32:06.563
pigeons, right?

00:32:08.938 --> 00:32:11.855
If you want a messenger,
ask another attorney.

00:32:12.730 --> 00:32:17.438
Even if you have money and power,
you're weak in front of the law.

00:32:28.146 --> 00:32:29.813
-Sakuma.
-Uh, yes?

00:32:30.855 --> 00:32:32.313
Do you know who I am?

00:32:33.021 --> 00:32:35.188
Of course, Mibu.

00:32:35.896 --> 00:32:37.188
Then,

00:32:38.105 --> 00:32:40.313
do you know how this world works?

00:32:41.146 --> 00:32:43.396
T-This world?

00:32:48.563 --> 00:32:49.688
Listen carefully.

00:32:53.771 --> 00:32:56.855
You meddled with something
you shouldn't have.

00:33:01.146 --> 00:33:03.271
Withdraw the police report right now.

00:33:04.230 --> 00:33:05.855
Y-Y-Yes.

00:33:09.021 --> 00:33:12.771
You said you don't choose your clients
based on their status

00:33:12.855 --> 00:33:14.938
or whether they're good or bad people.

00:33:16.105 --> 00:33:18.271
But Mr. Kyogoku's request is dangerous.

00:33:21.188 --> 00:33:23.855
It won't end with you
just losing your badge.

00:33:26.521 --> 00:33:27.688
One day,

00:33:28.313 --> 00:33:30.105
it could cost you your life.

00:33:38.980 --> 00:33:41.396
-Good morning.
-Morning. I'll visit the bar soon.

00:33:41.480 --> 00:33:43.063
Thank you. I'll be waiting.

00:33:43.146 --> 00:33:45.021
-Good morning.
-Morning.

00:33:45.105 --> 00:33:47.396
-Good morning.
-It's been a while. See you.

00:33:48.605 --> 00:33:50.063
You're popular.

00:33:50.146 --> 00:33:53.188
Well, I spend a lot of money.

00:33:53.271 --> 00:33:59.396
More importantly, that lawyer you
introduced me to is an interesting guy.

00:33:59.480 --> 00:34:00.480
Is that so?

00:34:00.563 --> 00:34:04.188
But why didn't you introduce me
to him right away?

00:34:04.688 --> 00:34:07.646
You were hogging a lawyer
who's quick on his feet.

00:34:08.146 --> 00:34:11.438
Since you already have a lawyer
who works with Fushimi-gumi,

00:34:11.521 --> 00:34:13.730
I felt it wasn't my place to say anything.

00:34:16.771 --> 00:34:21.688
Our lawyer lent me his phone
in the meeting room.

00:34:21.771 --> 00:34:25.063
But Attorney Kujo…

00:34:25.855 --> 00:34:27.063
Mr. Kyogoku,

00:34:27.146 --> 00:34:28.355
you know the police

00:34:28.438 --> 00:34:30.063
regularly check the call history

00:34:30.146 --> 00:34:32.105
of yakuza cell phones, right?

00:34:33.271 --> 00:34:35.605
If you use a cell phone here,

00:34:35.688 --> 00:34:36.980
it'd be a disadvantage,

00:34:37.063 --> 00:34:38.355
for me and also for you.

00:34:40.896 --> 00:34:45.438
We can establish self-defense,
regardless of a settlement agreement.

00:34:46.230 --> 00:34:48.188
If you and your bodyguards stay silent,

00:34:48.271 --> 00:34:50.813
you'll be cut loose in 20 days.

00:34:52.563 --> 00:34:57.271
But the other party agreed to a settlement
before the 20 days were up.

00:35:00.896 --> 00:35:02.313
Hey, Mibu.

00:35:03.771 --> 00:35:06.188
Something's bothering me.

00:35:08.480 --> 00:35:10.605
It's the first time

00:35:11.105 --> 00:35:14.146
I've been the target
of a snatch-and-grab in this city.

00:35:15.063 --> 00:35:18.563
I think someone is cooking something up

00:35:18.646 --> 00:35:22.646
to frame me.

00:35:31.313 --> 00:35:33.063
Am I overthinking it?

00:35:36.146 --> 00:35:37.980
What do you think, Mibu?

00:35:48.855 --> 00:35:50.146
Was it you?

00:35:50.230 --> 00:35:51.563
You cooked it up?

00:35:56.438 --> 00:35:59.146
You haven't forgotten
what happened that day, have you?

00:36:05.813 --> 00:36:07.230
Mibu.

00:36:08.896 --> 00:36:12.563
You guys have meddled with someone

00:36:12.646 --> 00:36:13.855
you shouldn't have.

00:36:16.021 --> 00:36:19.313
You stole the takings
from the gambling den we're looking after.

00:36:19.396 --> 00:36:20.855
Have you gone mad?

00:36:23.855 --> 00:36:25.688
The guy who was causing trouble

00:36:25.771 --> 00:36:28.563
immediately fessed up
that you were the mastermind.

00:36:30.188 --> 00:36:32.980
Thugs have no loyalty to their superiors.

00:36:37.313 --> 00:36:39.063
Yakuza don't fess up.

00:36:41.646 --> 00:36:45.271
But everyone loves themselves.

00:36:46.271 --> 00:36:48.396
"Egosurfing" is a search for love.

00:36:50.855 --> 00:36:52.396
By the way,

00:36:52.480 --> 00:36:53.855
this heater

00:36:53.938 --> 00:36:56.813
that dries the paint on cars…

00:36:57.521 --> 00:37:00.980
If you get too close to it,
your blood will boil, and you'll die.

00:37:01.063 --> 00:37:02.188
It's dangerous.

00:37:07.605 --> 00:37:10.855
Are you okay, Mibu?

00:37:11.355 --> 00:37:12.938
Is it hot?

00:37:17.146 --> 00:37:21.688
But you're too valuable
for me to let you die here.

00:37:21.771 --> 00:37:22.771
So what will you do?

00:37:22.855 --> 00:37:25.188
If you show your loyalty now,

00:37:25.688 --> 00:37:27.105
I'll forgive you this time.

00:37:27.688 --> 00:37:28.730
What do you say?

00:37:31.188 --> 00:37:32.480
I'm sorry.

00:37:34.563 --> 00:37:35.646
Please forgive me.

00:37:35.730 --> 00:37:38.438
Okay. Then show me your loyalty.

00:37:39.480 --> 00:37:41.063
What was it again?

00:37:41.146 --> 00:37:42.771
This dog… What's its name?

00:37:42.855 --> 00:37:45.438
Hey, stop it! Don't touch Rice Cake!

00:37:45.521 --> 00:37:47.438
Oh, right. It's Rice Cake.

00:37:47.521 --> 00:37:48.355
Rice Cake,

00:37:48.438 --> 00:37:50.438
the dog you've had since you were a kid.

00:37:50.521 --> 00:37:52.063
-Hey!
-Well…

00:37:55.730 --> 00:37:57.438
Kill it.

00:38:00.146 --> 00:38:01.896
There's no way I can do that!

00:38:05.771 --> 00:38:07.313
Then,

00:38:08.230 --> 00:38:09.396
die.

00:38:49.521 --> 00:38:50.771
Mibu,

00:38:52.105 --> 00:38:54.688
you chose to kill it.

00:38:56.146 --> 00:38:58.271
If you had killed it on my orders,

00:38:59.146 --> 00:39:02.021
you'd have just held a grudge against me.

00:39:10.271 --> 00:39:12.771
Bear the guilt of living
for the rest of your life.

00:39:35.938 --> 00:39:37.063
Is everything okay?

00:39:39.063 --> 00:39:40.271
Who are you?

00:39:48.771 --> 00:39:50.396
I'm Attorney Kujo.

00:39:53.063 --> 00:39:55.230
Please contact me if anything happens.

00:42:31.480 --> 00:42:36.480
Subtitle translation by: Miho Kunisawa